<h3>Advance</h3>
<p>Pathway students matriculate or apply to become official degree seeking students at BYU-Idaho by filling out the application at <a href="http://www.besmart.com/">www.besmart.com</a>. You can continue online and keep paying the reduce tuition rate or move to Rexburg and study on campus.</p>
<p>If you continue to take online classes you can start by earning <a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/Certificate Programs.pdf">Professional Certificates</a> while you work on your Associate or Bachelor degrees. Explore the <a href="x24375.xml">Online Degree website </a>to learn more about degree options.</p>
<h3>Steps to Matriculation:</h3>
<ol>
<li>Successfully complete Academic Start with at least a "B" average (<a href="http://www.byui.edu/online/online-support-center/faq#IDx28032">3.0 GPA</a>). </li>
<li><a href="x24381.xml">Apply</a> as a degree-seeking student.<ol>
<li>Agree to live by the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/StudentHonor/UniversityStandards.htm">honor code</a>.</li>
<li>Get an ecclesiastical endorsement from your Bishop and Stake President.</li>
<li>Complete online application.</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Browse available&nbsp;<a href="http://www.byui.edu/online/online-degrees-and-certificates">Online Degrees</a>. Find which one is right for you. </li>
<li>Work with your academic adviser to solidify your graduation plan.</li>
</ol>
